ams. We then take that information, add in our extensive experiences, and provide you with a vacation that will exceed your expectations. We are here to help you travel better.[/brando_accordian_content][brando_accordian_content accordian_title=\"Will my pop-up blocker affect how I use this website?\"]Many computer systems utilize \"pop-up blockers\" to prevent or limit online advertisements that sometimes appear when you use the internet. This web site uses pop-ups as a means to provide additional information, which you may find helpful in making informed travel decisions. We recommend you temporarily disable the blocker while utilizing this web site.[/brando_accordian_content][brando_accordian_content accordian_title=\"How early should I arrive to the airport?\"]You should arrive at the airport a minimum of two hours prior to departure for domestic flights, and three hours for international flights. We strongly recommend reconfirming your flight time 24 hours prior to departure, for both origin and destination flights.[/brando_accordian_content][brando_accordian_content accordian_title=\"What kind of documentation do I need to travel?\"]Before you may board a flight, all passengers 18 years of age and older are required to present photo ID issued by a government authority (example: drivers license or passport). If you don’t have either of those, please consult directly with the airline for alternatives. If you are traveling outside of the United States, all passengers are required to have a passport.[/brando_accordian_content][brando_accordian_content accordian_title=\" Do I need to reconfirm my flights before I leave?\"]It isn’t mandatory, but we highly encourage you to do so. Airlines regularly alter their schedules or change their flight numbers. We make every attempt to contact you when there is a change; however there are rare occasions when we are not correctly notified by the airlines that a change has occurred. Reconfirmation helps to detect a problem befo